.TH CUSTODIA-SERVER 1 "@DATE@" "Custodia @VERSION@" "Custodia Manual"
.SH NAME
custodia-server \- run the Custodia vault server
.SH SYNOPSIS
.SY custodia-server
.OP --config FILE
.YS
.SY custodia-server
.B version
.YS
.SY custodia-server
.B --version
.YS
.SY custodia-server
.B help
.YS
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B custodia-server
runs the Custodia vault API. The server stores opaque encrypted secret payloads,
authenticates clients with mTLS, records metadata and audit events, and never
handles application plaintext or application private encryption keys.
.PP
A normal build is universal and includes SQLite and PostgreSQL store support.
Select Lite or FULL behavior at runtime through configuration.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B version
Print build metadata and exit before loading configuration, logging, stores or
runtime services.
.TP
.B --version
Alias for
.BR version .
.TP
.B help, -h, --help
Print usage information and exit before runtime initialization.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI --config " FILE"
Path to the YAML configuration file.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B CUSTODIA_CONFIG_FILE
Configuration file path when
.B --config
is not provided.
.TP
.B CUSTODIA_STORE_BACKEND
Store backend. Use
.B sqlite
for Lite or
.B postgres
for PostgreSQL deployments.
.TP
.B CUSTODIA_SQLITE_PATH
SQLite database path for Lite deployments.
.TP
.B CUSTODIA_DATABASE_URL
PostgreSQL connection URL for FULL deployments.
.TP
.B CUSTODIA_TLS_CERT_FILE
Server TLS certificate.
.TP
.B CUSTODIA_TLS_KEY_FILE
Server TLS private key.
.TP
.B CUSTODIA_CLIENT_CA_FILE
Client CA bundle for mTLS authentication.
.TP
.B CUSTODIA_LOG_FILE
Log file path. Packaged installs default under
.IR /var/log/custodia .
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/custodia/config.yaml
Default packaged server configuration.
.TP
.I /etc/custodia/server.crt
Default TLS certificate for packaged Lite installs.
.TP
.I /etc/custodia/server.key
Default TLS private key for packaged Lite installs.
.TP
.I /etc/custodia/client-ca.crt
Default client CA bundle.
.TP
.I /var/lib/custodia/
Default state directory.
.TP
.I /var/log/custodia/custodia.log
Default packaged server log file.
.SH SYSTEMD
Packaged installs provide
.BR custodia.service .
Typical commands:
.PP
.EX
sudo systemctl enable --now custodia
sudo systemctl status custodia --no-pager
sudo journalctl -u custodia -f
.EE
.SH SECURITY NOTES
.B custodia-server
must not decrypt application secrets. Clients provide ciphertext, crypto
metadata and opaque recipient envelopes. Application cryptography is performed
by
.BR custodia-client (1)
or SDK clients outside the server process.
.PP
The packaged unit runs as the restricted
.B custodia
user and grants write access only to configured state/log paths.
.SH EXAMPLES
Start a packaged Lite service:
.PP
.EX
sudo systemctl enable --now custodia
.EE
.PP
Run a local development server with in-memory storage:
.PP
.EX
CUSTODIA_DEV_INSECURE_HTTP=true \\
CUSTODIA_STORE_BACKEND=memory \\
custodia-server
.EE
.PP
Check build metadata without runtime initialization:
.PP
.EX
custodia-server version
.EE
.SH VERSION
Custodia version: @VERSION@
.br
Build commit: @COMMIT@
.br
Build date: @DATE@
.PP
Runtime version is available with:
.PP
.EX
custodia-server version
.EE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Runtime or configuration failure.
.TP
.B 2
Usage error.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR custodia-admin (1),
.BR custodia-client (1),
.BR custodia-signer (1)
